Preparations for the South African Defence Forceâ€™s (SANDF) Armed Forces Day scheduled for Monday to Friday next week in in the city are at an advance stage.
Today (Thursday) SANDF officials were hard at work to finalise the static exhibit at the Polokwane Cricket Grounds.
Among the exciting events lined up are a military music concert, military displays and a night shoot demonstration.
Thabo Sello, Communication Officer from Department of Defence said learners from various secondary schools in the province have been invited to visit the exhibit in order to learn more about possible careers in the SANDF.
